name: Acting AG Matthew J. Platkin
tweet: It's normal to re-experience trauma during timeframes that are significant.  Like the birthday of a lost loved one, or during the holidays when someone's presence may be sorely missed.  No matter what feelings may be resurfacing, here are a few tips to help you cope and heal.  https://t.co/UdrGVOsgOK

name: Acting AG Matthew J. Platkin
tweet: The law enforcement community is no stranger to suicide.  Det. Santiago's untimely death 2 years ago today, motivated me to do something about it.  Today his memory lives on in every officer we help through our statewide resiliency program. Cops have our backs and we have theirs.  https://t.co/7i3rRbSW86
